  "text": "In this paper we show that a slicing approach is required to preserve continuity across sharp edges, and we present a new noise function based on Gabor noise [CITATION_1] ] that supports anisotropic filtering of sliced solid noise. We individually filter the slices of Gabor kernels. This requires the proper treatment of the phase of the kernel. We therefore introduce a new Gabor kernel, the phaseaugmented Gabor kernel. This, in turn, leads to our new noise function, random-phase Gabor noise. We also discuss how our derivations result in a generalization of the Projection-Slice Theorem as used by [CITATION_2] . We demonstrate that our new noise function supports both high-quality anti-aliasing and continuity across sharp edges, as well as anisotropy.",
